There have been numerous attempts to revitalize the neighborhood, including the construction of a modern shopping center on the corner of <a1_0><a1_1><a1_2><b6_0>Fresno and B streets<b6_0/><a1_2/><a1_1/><a1_0/>, an aborted attempt to build luxury homes and a golf course on the western edge of the neighborhood, and some new section 8 apartments have been built along <b7_0>Church Ave<b7_0/> west of Elm St. <a2_0><a2_1><a2_2>Cargill Meat Solutions and Foster Farms<a2_2/><a2_1/><a2_0/> both have large processing facilities in the neighborhood, and <b8_0>the stench<b8_0/> from these (and other small industrial facilities) has long plagued area residents.
